A former Navy SEAL who quit the army to become a woman took the stand today at a conference to discuss whether the U.S. military could one day allow openly transgender personnel.

Kristin Beck - formerly Chris Beck - was a senior chief in the SEALs with more than 20 years' service when she retired in 2011 to pursue her life as a woman.

And today, having completely transformed from her old self, she was a guest at a conference where  attendees gathered from 18 countries whose armed forces do allow transgender soldiers.

