It is estimated that there are some 15,500 transgender people in the U.S. military already, who conceal the fact in order to keep their careers. At present it is Pentagon policy to discharge transgender people who are discovered.

Speaking to the event today, Beck said: 'I was in the middle of the toughest of the tough as a Navy SEAL. And I could still do that today, as a female.

'Females are strong. Females chew tobacco and smoke cigars. They lift weights'

After a pause, she added: 'I still have the ability to kick ass,' according to the Daily Beast.

